  "text": "The Hamilton Rating Scale for Depression (HAM-D) is not a self-reporting measure, but a commonly used interviewer-administered rating scale of depressive symptoms. It is used to gauge the severity of depression in patients already diagnosed with depressive disorders [CITATION_1] . Its original 21 items were used with a cutoff score of seven or higher as recommended for identifying depression.",
